{"cursor":"77552","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n and/or 'Soka Gakkai International' ('SGI') is a lay Buddhist movement linking\n more than 12 million people around the world, and is currently described as\n \"the most diverseâ Tricycle Magazine Interview: http:-\n //www.daisakuikeda.org/sub/resources/interview/interview2/2008tricycle.html and âthe largest Lay Buddhist movement in the world.â Members of\n the SGI integrate their Buddhist practice into their daily lives, following the\n Lotus Sutra based teachings of Nichiren, a 13th-century Japanese Buddhist\n priest. Founded by educator TsunesaburÅ Makiguchi in 1930, the organization was\n suppressed during World War II for its opposition to the Japanese governmentâs\n consolidation of religious groups. A significant\n comrade of Makiguchi, JÅsei Toda, who was released from prison in July 1945,\n took a leading role of responsibility for the organisation. In the following\n years, starting from 1951, he reformed the membership base of Soka Gakkai's\n 3,000 families to include more than 750,000 families before his death in 1958.\n\nFurther expansion of the movement was led by its third president Daisaku Ikeda,\nwho founded the Soka Gakkai International on January 26, 1975 on the island of\nGuam [http://www.sgi.org/about-us/history-of-sgi/history-of-sgi.html History\nof SGI] The Soka Gakkai International (SGI) currently consists of 84\nconstituent organizations and has 12 million members in 192 countries and\nterritories worldwide.\n\nSGI has established schools inside and outside Japan [http://www.daisakuikeda.org/main/educator/edu-instit/soka-\nschools.html Education: Soka Schools | Daisaku Ikeda Website ] including\nuniversities, [http://www.soka.ac.jp/en/index.html Soka University | Home ][http://www.soka.edu/admission_aid/ We\nappreciate your interest in Soka University of America! - Admission Aid - Soka\nUniversity of America ] Min-On Music Association, [http://www.min-on.org/index.php/about-min-on/who-we-\nare About Min-On : Who We Are - Min-On Concert Association ] Tokyo Fuji Art Museum, [http://www.fujibi.or.jp/en/exhibitions/now-\nshowing.html Now Showing | TOKYO FUJI ART MUSEUM ] Toda Institute for Global Peace [http://www.toda.org/ Toda\nInstitute for Global Peace and Policy Research ] and The Institute of Oriental Philosophy. [http://www.iop.or.jp/\nThe Institute of Oriental Philosophy-Home ] In\n1981 the Soka Gakkai was registered as an NGO at the United\nNations. [http://www.peoplesdecade.org/about/overview/ Overview | People's\nDecade for Nuclear Abolition ][http://www.theglobalexperts.org/experts/expertise-region/north-\namerica-expertise-region/hiro-sakurai-2 Hiro Sakurai - Global Experts ]\n\nThe growth of SGI membership has been attributed in part to the organization's\ntradition of small group, neighborhood and local community discussion\nmeetings. Metraux, SERA 2007, p. 157-72\n","linknr":1329,"url":"Sōka_Gakkai","recorded":1375054444,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Soka_Gakkai&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Soka_Gakkai&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Soka_Gakkai","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=S%C5%8Dka_Gakkai&redirect=no","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:Sanshokuki2.svg","//